<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Tourism - Explore Malta</title>
    <style>
        /* ==========================================
           Configurações Gerais (Mantendo o Padrão)
           ========================================== */
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Georgia, serif;
        }

        body {
            background-color: #fcf8f2; /* Creme suave */
            color: #4a3f35; /* Marrom escuro */
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* Botão Voltar Fixo e Discreto */
        .back-btn {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            background-color: #f4ece1;
            border: 1px solid #e6dac8;
            color: #4a3f35;
            text-decoration: none;
            padding: 10px 18px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
            z-index: 10;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
        }

        .back-btn:hover {
            background-color: #ebe0cf;
            transform: translateX(-3px);
        }

        /* Cabeçalho */
        .header-section {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 100px 20px 40px 20px;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .header-section h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #8c7864;
            font-weight: 400;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .header-section p {
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            color: #706356;
            font-style: italic;
        }

        /* Container Principal */
        .main-container {
            max-width: 1000px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* ==========================================
           Blocos de Destinos Turísticos
           ========================================== */
        .destination-card {
            background-color: #f4ece1; /* Bege calcário */
            border: 1px solid #e6dac8;
            border-radius: 12px;
            overflow: hidden;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(140, 120, 100, 0.05);
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        /* Exibição da Imagem Panorâmica */
        .destination-image-wrapper {
            width: 100%;
            height: 300px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .destination-image-wrapper img {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            object-fit: cover;
            transition: transform 0.4s ease;
        }

        .destination-card:hover .destination-image-wrapper img {
            transform: scale(1.02);
        }

        /* Conteúdo do Texto */
        .destination-info {
            padding: 30px;
        }

        .destination-info h2 {
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            color: #735e49;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }

        .location-tag {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #dfcfbe;
            color: #5c4f43;
            padding: 3px 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .destination-text {
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: #4a3f35;
            text-align: justify;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Link para retornar à Home -->
    <a href="index.html" class="back-btn">← Back to Home</a>

    <header class="header-section">
        <h1>Wonders of Malta</h1>
        <p>Discover breathtaking fortresses, ancient alleys, and vibrant coastal paths.</p>
    </header>

    <main class="main-container">

        <!-- Destino 1: Valletta (História) -->
        <section class="destination-card">
            <div class="destination-image-wrapper">
                <img src="valeta.png" alt="Valletta Cityscape">
            </div>
            <div class="destination-info">
                <h2>Valletta: The Fortress Capital</h2>
                <div class="location-tag">📍 South Eastern Region</div>
                <p class="destination-text">
                    Founded in 1566 by the Grand Master of the Knights of St. John, Jean de Valette, Valletta is a UNESCO World Heritage site and a masterpiece of Baroque architecture. This open-air museum is protected by massive stone bastions built to guard the majestic Grand Harbour. Walking down its steep streets reveals historic palaces, grand fountains, and beautiful limestone walls that tell centuries of heroic Mediterranean tales.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Destino 2: Mdina / Hidden Gems (Sugerido para image3jpg.jpeg) -->
        <section class="destination-card">
            <div class="destination-image-wrapper">
                <img src="image3jpg.jpeg" alt="Historic Maltese Architecture">
            </div>
            <div class="destination-info">
                <h2>Mdina & The Silent Fortresses</h2>
                <div class="location-tag">📍 Northern Region / Central Malta</div>
                <p class="destination-text">
                    Beyond the coast, Malta’s heart is shaped by ancient citadel alleys and narrow medieval corridors. Walking through these silent golden-limestone gateways feels like stepping back in time. These structures showcase traditional wooden balconies and detailed architecture, providing panoramic views that stretch across the entire island.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Destino 3: St. Julian's Promenade -->
        <section class="destination-card">
            <div class="destination-image-wrapper">
                <img src="st-julians1.png" alt="St. Julian's Promenade">
            </div>
            <div class="destination-info">
                <h2>St. Julian's Promenade</h2>
                <div class="location-tag">📍 Eastern Coastline</div>
                <p class="destination-text">
                    St. Julian's perfectly balances traditional fishing charm with a lively, modern coastline. The coastal promenade is a major highlight, stretching along the sea and connecting Spinola Bay to Balluta Bay. Filled with lively open-air restaurants, cafes, and colorful traditional boats (luzzu), it is the ideal spot for long evening walks by the crashing waves and experiencing Malta's energetic coastal lifestyle.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

</body>
</html>
